25:29.864 --> 25:37.112
nights. This is Now, April 12, 1963. So I exposed a 
four-end plate to Mars for, I don't know, over the

25:41.432 --> 25:46.920
order of three hours. I don't remember the exact 
exposure time. And we got a spectrogram, and I was

25:50.204 --> 25:52.388
going to start another one. Mars was at 
quadrature, of course, to get the velocity, but I

25:54.310 --> 25:58.436
guess it was far enough north that you could do more 
