27:01.105 --> 27:04.110
the water lines visually. And maybe they'll show 
up. By golly, I think they did, especially over one

27:06.562 --> 27:11.550
third of the exposure. I'm not sure I knew exactly 
which way it was up at the time. I had to figure out

27:14.735 --> 27:16.498
which polar cap it was. But they were there. But the 
outstanding thing was not noticed until about a

27:18.922 --> 27:23.710
week later. And for some reason, I decided to 
compare the spectrum of Mars to a Venus spectrum

27:24.247 --> 27:33.377
that I had from the same instrument taken by Dunham 
a long time ago. And of course, the quality of the

27:33.757 --> 27:37.521
new one, especially on a 4N, was far greater. But 
the nice thing about the Venus old spectrum was

27:37.822 --> 27:44.949
that it showed me where the 8689 carbon dioxide 
band was located. And by golly, when I looked at the

27:45.510 --> 27:50.035
Mars spectrum, there were the lines, much, much 
weaker, but unmistakable. And you could match

27:52.459 --> 27:53.760
them line for line. Yeah, it just blew me away. So I 
went hooping and hollering around the trailers,

27:56.023 --> 28:01.809
found Kaplan right away, had him look at it. He 
wasn't much used to looking at spectra, but he

28:01.829 --> 28:04.151
could see it too. And then called up Guido. He 
refused to believe it for a few minutes. I don't

28:09.516 --> 28:19.026
remember if he came up to look the same afternoon or 
the next day, but we knew right away that that meant

28:09.516 --> 28:19.026
that there was more carbon dioxide on Mars than 
people had reckoned before by a lot. Because this

28:22.745 --> 28:24.027
was intrinsically. It's a weak band. It doesn't 
depend very much on the gas pressure. Total gas

28:28.172 --> 28:31.156
pressure is mostly just dependent on the column of 
carbon dioxide. So it's an unavoidable

28:31.557 --> 28:35.603
conclusion that there had to be more CO2. So either 
there had to be more atmosphere on Mars than anyone

28:36.203 --> 28:43.133
thought, or the atmosphere, if thin, had to be 
predominantly carbon dioxide. And those were

28:43.153 --> 28:47.359
conclusions one could work out in your head 
without even calculating a number. So that was

28:48.773 --> 28:54.261
